4.1. Development process of shale gas in China
China has experienced 3 shale gas development stages in
the period to tackle key problems for more than 10 years:
cooperation and reference stage, exploration and evaluation
stage, construction and production stage on a scale.
4.1.1. Cooperation and reference stage (2003e2009)
China introduced basic concept of shale gas in the stage,
with increasing attention paid to shale gas as a kind of resource.
Some domestic scholars began to use successful experience in
the US for reference and introduce concept of shale gas [38,39]
and also predict prospect of shale gas resource in China. In
2005, China Research Institute of Petroleum Exploration and
Development set up shale gas project group to start evaluation
of new progress in shale gas in North America and screening of
favorable area for shale gas in China. In 2007, China Research
Institute of Petroleum Exploration and Development and
Newfield Exploration Company signed a foreign cooperation
agreement on joint research of shale gas in Weiyuan Region.
Shale gas team of China Research Institute of Petroleum
Exploration and Development drilled the first geological in-
formation well for shale gas on north flank of geological
structure in Changning in China, namely Well Changxin 1 to
determine the situation for exploration and development of
shale gas in Wufeng Formation-Longmaxi Formation in
Sichuan Basin and the surrounding region [40]. Petro China
gave an official and written reply to Work Program for
Demonstration Zone for Oil and Shale Gas Industrialization in
China to start construction of demonstration zone for shale gas
industrialization in Chingning, Weiyuan and Zhaotong and
present that construction target was up to 15  108 m3/a.
4.1.2. Exploration and evaluation stage (2010e2013)
In the stage, many petroleum companies determined po-
tential and development prospect of shale gas resource by
drilling evaluation and made certain development position of
marine shale gas in Wufang Formation-Longmaxi Formation
in Middle and Upper Yangtze Region and discovered two
major shale gas fields in Shunan and Fuling [41], having laid a
foundation for development of shale gas on a scale.
Petro China targeted the marine shale gas resource in
