4.2. Typical gas field development case
4.2.1. Shunan Shale Gas Field
Shunan Shale Gas Field is primarily located in Sichuan
Province and composed of 3 blocks in Weiyuan, Changning and
Zhaotong, with organic rich shale in Wufeng Formation-
Longmaxi Formation as target stratum. Weiyuan Block is
located in low fold belt of paleo-mesozoic slope in the southwest
of Sichuan Province, covering an area of about 7600 km2, being
from 2000m to 4500 m in burial depth of reservoir, from 40 m to
60 m in thickness, from 2.5% to 8.5% in TOC, from 2.5% to
3.8% in Ro value, from 3.4% to 8.5% in total porosity, from 1.2 to
2.1 in formation pressure coefficient; Changning and Zhaotong
Blocks are located on south flank of Changning Tectonics,
covering an area of 3400 km2, being from 2000m to 3000 m in
burial depth of reservoir, from 15 m to 25 m in thickness, from
2.7% to 8.5% in TOC, 2.8% in Ro value, from 3.4% to 8.2%in
total porosity, from 1.3 to 2.0 in formation pressure coefficient.
The gas field is 0.8  104 km2 in total area, with recoverable
reserves for shale gas up to 1.0  1012 m3, proven reserve up to
1635  108 m3. Typical well is from 2500 m to 3500 m invertical
depth, from 1500 m to 1800 m in horizontal section length,
subjecting to volume fracturing in 15e20 stages. The single well
is 9  104 m3/d in initial output and 1.0  108 m3 in ultimate
recoverable reserves. By the end of 2016, the production ca-
pacity was up to 30  108 m3/a, with annual output in 2016 up to
28  108 m3, it is estimated that the shale gas output is up to
30  108 m3 in 2017.
Ning 201-H1 horizontal well was drilled Changning Block
in 2012, with test output up to 15  104 m3/d. The multi-well
pad test on H2 and H3 Platforms including 14 (8  6) wells
was started in 2013, with YS108H1-1 horizontal well drilled
in Zhaotong Block and test output up to 20.86  104 m3/d. In
2014, Well Wei 204 was drilled in Weiyuan Block, with test
output up to 16.5  104 m3/d after change from straight well to
horizontal well. In 2016, Sinopec planed to start construction
of production capacity up to 120  108 m3/a of shale gas, it is
estimated that the shale gas output shall be more than
100  108 m3 in 2020; by the end of 2016, there were 93
horizontal wells and 85 put-to-production wells in Weiyuan,
with annual output up to 11.8  108 m3 in 2016; there were 66
horizontal wells and 57 put-to-production wells in Changning
