5.3.2. An overall breakthrough to be made in core
technology and equipment for marine shale at the depth of
more than 3500 m
Marine shale gas resource in Wufeng Formation-Longmaxi
Formation is more than 3500 m in burial depth of main body.
10 areas of mining right of Petro China in Sichuan Basin are
taken as example, the shale gas resources at the depth of no more
than 4500 m in the area of 6.4  104 km2 are 16.3  1012 m3,
including 11.2  1012 m3 at the depth of more than 3500 m,
accounting for 69% of resources. The deep shale reservoir is
characterized by high temperature, high stress and high plas-
ticity, with difficulty in well completion and volume trans-
formation for horizontal well for shale gas to a great extent.
There are many wells drilled down to the depth of more than
3500 m in some blocks, but the test results therein are poor [55].
It is necessary to carry out evaluation of area selected for shale
gas at the depth of more than 3500 m to determine a number of
deep areas for development and construction and tackle key
problems in important engineering technology and equipment
for shale gas in deep area to grasp the applicable technologies
and establish pilot test area for development of deep shale gas
and promote effective development of deep shale gas on a scale.
5.3.3. Production mode of multi-well pad for complex
surface condition to be established
The single well for shale gas is characterized by higher
initial output and quick decrease in output and long stable
production period, therefore, it is necessary to drill a large
number of wells to stabilize and increase production in
development of shale gas field. The shale gas fields developed
are mainly distributed in picturesque and populous regions in
the south, with strict requirement of environmental protection,
in addition, these regions are complex in topography, densely
populated, less per capita cultivated land. In order to reduce
the land for well site, cluster horizontal well group is pre-
vailing to carry out multi-well pad operation, with 6e10
wells drilled per pad in most cases. In multi-stage fracturing
construction, the operation efficiency is greatly improved by
optimization of operation process and the drilling fluid and
flow-back fluid in fracturing are subjected recycling, drilling
cuttings are subjected to harmless disposal to ensure safety
and environmental protection in development of shale gas. It is
also necessary to further optimize multi-well pad operation
mode to increase number of cluster horizontal wells per pad
and further enhance land use rate for well site.
5.3.4. Long well construction period and high cost in
development of shale gas
It is observed from data on shale gas development that the
entire period from investment to gas well production shall be
from 1.5 to 2 years. The non-operation time is in excess of
50% of well construction period. China is complex in surface
and geologic conditions for shale gas, with large workload,
long period and high cost for shale gas well construction.
Shale gas resources are primarily in mountain, desert and loess
tableland, with longer construction period for well site; shale
gas reservoir is under complex crustal stress, with difficulty in
horizontal well completion and volume transformation, at
present, the period for single horizontal well completion in
1500 m of horizontal section is from 60 d to 80 d, it is
advisable to further reduce cost.
6. Economy and prospect of global shale gas development
Low oil and gas prices compel all enterprises engaging in
shale gas business to intensify their cost control, with updating
and upgrading of key technologies to improve development ef-
fect and multi-well pad to greatly operation efficiency and
achieve self cost revolution in development of shale oil and
gas. Henry Hub Data Center in the US shows that since natural
gas price was down to RMB 0.46/m3 [57], it should be on the low
side, and now, the natural gas price is RMB 0.8/m3 (June, 2017).
Marcellus Shale Gas Field is taken as an example, there were
there were 141 drilling machines in operation in peak period in
Jan. 2012, and then, with the increase of gas price, the number of
drilling machines was down to 24 in June, 2016, and then the
number of which bounced back to 45 [58]. Although the number
of drilling machines was on the decrease to a great extent, due to
improvement in the construction level and operation efficiency.
The gas field output was increased from 17764  104 m3/d in
Jan.2012 from 50873  104 m3/d to 50873  104 m3/d in July,
2016. The output was increased to 54701  104 m3/d [59] in June
2017 [60]. At present, the break even point for shale gas fields in
the US is from USD 0.58 to 0.91/m3 [60], therefore, there is
economic benefit in development of shale gas although the
natural gas price is low. Marcellus Shale Gas Field is taken as an
example, in case that the single well is USD 4 million in in-
vestment cost and (EUR) 1.06  108 m3 in ultimate recoverable
reserves, it is estimated that its internal rate of return is 9.1%
[61]. The natural gas price in China has been on the decrease
since 2012 under the influence of international natural gas
market, with further improvement in engineering technology,
market mechanism, management mode, policy support, China
shall gradually highlight economic and social benefits in
development of shale gas industry.
There are abundant shale gas resources in the world, with
output on the rapid growth. In 2016, global shale gas output was
up to 5068  108 m3, including 4447  108 m3 in the US,
510  108 m3 in Canada, 78  108 m3 in China and 18  108 m3
in Argentina. EIA (2016) predicts that global shale gas output
shall be up to 1.7  1012m3, including 8200  108m3in the US,
2200  108 m3 in China, 730  108 m3 in Canada, 730  108 m3
in Mexico, 670  108 m3 in Algeria, 650  108 m3 in Argentina
and 3720  108 m3 [62] in other regions.
